<MELItem itemNbr="21-26-03" id="X-BOEING:FTID:81205.787.DDG.CU.MEL.2-21-26-03.1.2-21-26-03">
<Title>Lavatory/Galley Ventilation PECS Liquid Heat Exchanger Barrier Filter</Title>
<DispatchCondition repairInterval="C" nbrInstalled="1" nbrRequired="0" maintIndicator="(M)">
<DispatchConditionRemarks>
<Para>May be inoperative provided lavatory/galley flow and temperature sensor is deactivated.</Para>
</DispatchConditionRemarks>
<Note>
<Para>Deactivation of lavatory/galley flow and temperature sensor results in display of LAVATORY/GALLEY FLOW DET status message.  The airplane must also be dispatched using MEL item 21-26-02.</Para>
</Note>
<DispatchProcedure>
<MaintenanceProcedure>
<Para>Deactivate lavatory/galley flow and temperature sensor and, if desired, remove filter (AMM DDG 21-26-03).</Para>
<List listType="1.">
<ListItem>
<Para>Using a flight deck multi-function display only, open the LAV GALLEY FLOW	 DET circuit breaker and lock with an INOP tag.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Note>
<Para>LAVATORY/GALLEY FLOW DET status message will be displayed.  The airplane must also be dispatched using MEL item 21-26-02.</Para>
</Note>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>If desired, a dirty or clogged filter may be removed:</Para>
<List listType="A.">
<ListItem>
<Para>Open the following circuit breakers and lock with an DO NOT CLOSE tag:</Para>
<List listType="1)">
<ListItem>
<Para>MC LAV GALLEY FAN 1</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>MC LAV GALLEY FAN 2</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>LAV GALLEY FAN 1</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>LAV GALLEY FAN 2</Para>
</ListItem>
</List>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>Gain access to lav/galley filter.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>Remove filter.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>Close the following circuit breakers:</Para>
<List listType="1)">
<ListItem>
<Para>MC LAV GALLEY FAN 1</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>MC LAV GALLEY FAN 2</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>LAV GALLEY FAN 1</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>LAV GALLEY FAN 2</Para>
</ListItem>
</List>
</ListItem>
</List>
</ListItem>
</List>
</MaintenanceProcedure>
</DispatchProcedure>
</DispatchCondition>
</MELItem>
